<subSubSection id="C36082F2A504FF9AFF26FDE6FAAEFCBE" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC5D179A504FF9AFF26FDE6FAAEFCBE" blockId="14.[151,1437,598,2016]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFF26FDE6FE8CFDC5" bold="true" box="[151,281,598,624]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Shell smooth, with microstriae and a single incised line at periphery; pseudumbilicus adjacent to columella. Penis simple, lacking mamilliform glands and glandular disc, sperm duct closed as a tube. Pallial oviduct contains an additional gland around egg groove at posterior end of straight section (anterior to translucent capsule gland); copulatory bursa opens at anterior end of straight section. Radula lacks flange on outer side of base of outer marginal tooth. Caribbean Sea, Gulf of Mexico, Gulf of 
<collectingCountry id="F36D91E9A504FF9AFBD2FD41FB22FCBE" box="[1123,1207,753,779]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Guinea</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F36D91E9A504FF9AFB6CFD41FAA2FCBE" box="[1245,1335,753,779]" name="Angola" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Angola</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36082F2A504FF9BFF77FCA7FBEAFD7A" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC5D179A504FF9AFF77FCA7FDBBFA76" blockId="14.[151,1437,598,2016]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFF77FCA7FED4FC84" bold="true" box="[198,321,791,817]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks:</emphasis>
This subgenus was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFD6CFCA8FC3AFC87" author="Rosewater, J." box="[733,943,792,818]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="7 - 48" refId="ref71743" refString="Rosewater, J. (1981) The family Littorinidae in tropical West Africa. Atlantide Report, 13, 7 - 48." type="journal article" year="1981">Rosewater (1981)</bibRefCitation>
for the 
<typeStatus id="54C16FDBA504FF9AFBBFFCA8FBD5FC87" box="[1038,1088,792,818]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
species ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFB1EFCA8FE9EFCED" authorityName="Potiez &amp; Michaud" authorityYear="1838" class="Gastropoda" family="Phasianellidae" genus="Phasianella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meleagris" subGenus="Fossarilittorina">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFB1EFCA8FE9EFCED" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">L. (Fossarilittorina) meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, based on the distinctive character of the umbilicate shell with a resemblance to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFF26FCD5FE97FCCB" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1841" box="[151,258,869,894]" class="Gastropoda" family="Planaxidae" genus="Fossarus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFF26FCD5FE97FCCB" box="[151,258,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fossarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The radula was not described in detail, but was said to resemble that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFBECFCD5FAFCFCCB" authorityName="Reid &amp; Williams" authorityYear="2004" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1117,1385,869,894]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Melarhaphe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="neritoides">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFBECFCD5FAFCFCCB" box="[1117,1385,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Melarhaphe neritoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the implication being that it differed from those of other species now included in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFBEBFC3CFA98FC10" authorityName="Habe" authorityYear="1956" box="[1114,1293,908,933]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFBEBFC3CFA98FC10" box="[1114,1293,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Echinolittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Rosewater suggested that other possible members might include the species now classified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFB28FC02FAA3FC7E" baseAuthorityName="Muhlfeld" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[1177,1334,946,971]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mespillum">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFB28FC02FAA3FC7E" box="[1177,1334,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. mespillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFEE6FC69FE46FC47" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[343,467,985,1010]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="porcata">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFEE6FC69FE46FC47" box="[343,467,985,1010]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. porcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in the eastern Pacific (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFCD1FC69FC79FC46" author="Reid, D. G." box="[864,1004,985,1011]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="259 - 281" refId="ref71006" refString="Reid, D. G. (2002 a) Morphological review and phylogenetic analysis of Nodilittorina Gastropoda: Littorinidae). Journal of Molluscan Studies, 68, 259 - 281." type="journal article" year="2002">Reid 2002a</bibRefCitation>
). Subsequently, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFB1DFC69FAF0FC47" authorityName="Rosewater" authorityYear="1981" box="[1196,1381,985,1010]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Fossarilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFB1DFC69FAF0FC47" box="[1196,1381,985,1010]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fossarilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was treated as a full genus by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFE68FBB0FCB3FBAF" author="Bandel, K. &amp; Kadolsky, D." box="[473,806,1024,1050]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 42" refId="ref64804" refString="Bandel, K. &amp; Kadolsky, D. (1982) Western Atlantic species of Nodilittorina (Gastropoda: Prosobranchia): comparative morphology and its functional, ecological, phylogenetic and taxonomic implications. Veliger, 25, 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="1982">Bandel &amp; Kadolsky (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, who included a description of the penis among its defining characters. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFE34FB96FD84FBF5" author="Reid, D. G." box="[389,529,1062,1088]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref70736" refString="Reid, D. G. (1986) The Littorinid Molluscs of Mangrove Forests in the Indo-Pacific Region: the Genus Littoraria. British Museum (Natural History), London, xv + 228 pp." type="book" year="1986">Reid (1986)</bibRefCitation>
also accepted this as a full genus, and in an early cladistic analysis concluded that it was the sister of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFE07FBFDFDD1FBD3" authorityName="Menke" authorityYear="1828" box="[438,580,1101,1126]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Melarhaphe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFE07FBFDFDD1FBD3" box="[438,580,1101,1126]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Melarhaphe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on synapomorphies of the penis. As a result of a more detailed phylogenetic analysis of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFE6DFBC4FDF3FB3B" authorityName="Children" authorityYear="1834" box="[476,614,1140,1166]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Littorinidae</taxonomicName>
based on anatomical and shell characters, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFB14FBC4FAA9FB3B" author="Reid, D. G." box="[1189,1340,1140,1166]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref70861" refString="Reid, D. G. (1989) The comparative morphology, phylogeny and evolution of the gastropod family Littorinidae. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London, Series B, 324, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1989">Reid (1989)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFF26FB2BFEC5FB01" authorityName="Rosewater" authorityYear="1981" box="[151,336,1179,1204]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Fossarilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFF26FB2BFEC5FB01" box="[151,336,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fossarilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFD8EFB2BFD4DFB01" authorityName=", Bandel &amp; Kadolsky" authorityYear="1982" box="[575,728,1179,1204]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Nodilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFD8EFB2BFD4DFB01" box="[575,728,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Nodilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ (then including species now assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFB50FB2BFA01FB01" authorityName="Habe" authorityYear="1956" box="[1249,1428,1179,1204]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFB50FB2BFA01FB01" box="[1249,1428,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Echinolittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFF26FB71FED1FB6F" authorityName="Rosewater" authorityYear="1970" box="[151,324,1217,1242]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Austrolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFF26FB71FED1FB6F" box="[151,324,1217,1242]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Austrolittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFEE4FB71FE7DFB6F" authorityName="S. Williams, D. Reid &amp; Littlewood" authorityYear="2003" box="[341,488,1217,1242]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Afrolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFEE4FB71FE7DFB6F" box="[341,488,1217,1242]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Afrolittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFD97FB71FD2AFB6F" authorityName=", Bandel &amp; Kadolsky" authorityYear="1982" box="[550,703,1217,1242]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Nodilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFD97FB71FD2AFB6F" box="[550,703,1217,1242]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Nodilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23DB010A504FF9AFD78FB71FD79FB6E" box="[713,748,1217,1243]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFD78FB71FD72FB6F" box="[713,743,1217,1242]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">s.s</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), and included within it only 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFBE8FB71FB7AFB6F" authorityName="Potiez &amp; Michaud" authorityYear="1838" box="[1113,1263,1217,1242]" class="Gastropoda" family="Phasianellidae" genus="Phasianella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFBE8FB71FB7AFB6F" box="[1113,1263,1217,1242]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFAB1FB71FA09FB6F" baseAuthorityName="Muhlfeld" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[1280,1436,1217,1242]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mespillum">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFAB1FB71FA09FB6F" box="[1280,1436,1217,1242]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. mespillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and doubtfully 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFEE4FB58FD2FFAB7" authority="(Philippi, 1846 a)" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[341,698,1256,1282]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFEE4FB58FE48FAB4" box="[341,477,1256,1281]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. modesta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFE43FB58FD27FAB7" author="Philippi, R. A." box="[498,690,1256,1282]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="138 - 143" refId="ref70302" refString="Philippi, R. A. (1846 a) Descriptions of a new species of Trochus, and of eighteen new species of Littorina, in the collection of H. Cuming, Esq. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1845, 138 - 143." type="journal article" year="1846">Philippi, 1846a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This result was further refined by a species-level cladistic analysis of ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFE94FABFFE2BFA9D" authority="(Reid 2002b)" authorityName=", Bandel &amp; Kadolsky" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Reid" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[293,446,1295,1320]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Nodilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFE94FABFFE2BFA9D" box="[293,446,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Nodilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFE66FABEFDF1FA9D" author="Reid, D. G." box="[471,612,1294,1320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="85 - 169" refId="ref71039" refString="Reid, D. G. (2002 b) The genus Nodilittorina von Martens, 1897 (Gastropoda: Littorinidae) in the eastern Pacific Ocean, with a discussion of biogeographic provinces of the rocky-shore fauna. Veliger, 45, 85 - 169." type="journal article" year="2002">Reid 2002b</bibRefCitation>
), which restricted the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFC68FABFFB07FA9D" authorityName="Rosewater" authorityYear="1981" box="[985,1170,1295,1320]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Fossarilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFC68FABFFB07FA9D" box="[985,1170,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fossarilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFB06FABFFADEFA9D" authorityName="Potiez &amp; Michaud" authorityYear="1838" box="[1207,1355,1295,1320]" class="Gastropoda" family="Phasianellidae" genus="Phasianella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFB06FABFFADEFA9D" box="[1207,1355,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFA32FABFFE9AFAFB" baseAuthorityName="Muhlfeld" baseAuthorityYear="1824" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mespillum">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFA32FABFFE9AFAFB" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. mespillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although this analysis produced a poorly-resolved phylogeny, in all trees this pair of species appeared in a relatively basal position, sister to all other ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFC83FAECFC5EFAC0" authorityName=", Bandel &amp; Kadolsky" authorityYear="1982" box="[818,971,1372,1397]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Nodilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFC83FAECFC5EFAC0" box="[818,971,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Nodilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFC52FAECFBDEFAC0" baseAuthorityName="Reid" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[995,1099,1372,1397]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Littorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFC52FAECFBDEFAC0" box="[995,1099,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Littorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and some other genera. This exclusion from ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFEEBFA33FE66FA29" authorityName=", Bandel &amp; Kadolsky" authorityYear="1982" box="[346,499,1411,1436]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Nodilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFEEBFA33FE66FA29" box="[346,499,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Nodilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ was a consequence of the simple penis and outer marginal teeth of the radula, interpreted as plesiomorphic traits.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC5D179A504FF9AFF77FA60FC10F8D8" blockId="14.[151,1437,598,2016]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Three molecular studies have included one or more species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFC1AFA60FBF1FA5C" authorityName="Rosewater" authorityYear="1981" box="[939,1124,1488,1513]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Fossarilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFC1AFA60FBF1FA5C" box="[939,1124,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fossarilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In a Bayesian analysis of all littorinine subgenera based on four gene fragments, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFC81FA47FC52F9A5" authorityName="Potiez &amp; Michaud" authorityYear="1838" box="[816,967,1527,1552]" class="Gastropoda" family="Phasianellidae" genus="Phasianella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFC81FA47FC52F9A5" box="[816,967,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fell within a clade of six exemplars of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFF26F9ADFCA0F982" authority="(Williams, Reid &amp; Littlewood 2003)" baseAuthorityName="Williams, Reid &amp; Littlewood" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[151,821,1565,1591]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFF26F9ADFEDFF983" box="[151,330,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Echinolittorina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFED5F9ADFCB9F982" author="Williams, S. T. &amp; Reid, D. G. &amp; Littlewood, D. T. J." box="[356,812,1565,1591]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="60 - 86" refId="ref73842" refString="Williams, S. T., Reid, D. G. &amp; Littlewood, D. T. J. (2003) A molecular phylogeny of the Littorininae (Gastropoda: Littorinidae): unequal evolutionary rates, morphological parallelism and biogeography of the Southern Ocean. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 28, 60 - 86." type="journal article" year="2003">Williams, Reid &amp; Littlewood 2003</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This was confirmed by an analysis of all 59 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFF26F9F4FE32F9EB" box="[151,423,1604,1630]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFF26F9F4FEDFF9E8" box="[151,330,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Echinolittorina</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
then known (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFDFAF9F4FCCBF9EB" author="Williams, S. T. &amp; Reid, D. G." box="[587,862,1604,1630]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="2227 - 2251" refId="ref73800" refString="Williams, S. T. &amp; Reid, D. G. (2004) Speciation and diversity on tropical rocky shores: a global phylogeny of snails of the genus Echinolittorina. Evolution, 58, 2227 - 2251." type="journal article" year="2004">Williams &amp; Reid 2004</bibRefCitation>
), but the basal branching order within the genus was not resolved. In the latest analysis (Bayesian inference using Beast program) 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFBE3F9DBFA9EF931" authorityName="Rosewater" authorityYear="1981" box="[1106,1291,1643,1668]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Fossarilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFBE3F9DBFA9EF931" box="[1106,1291,1643,1668]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fossarilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appeared as the basal branch of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFE24F921FDDDF91F" baseAuthorityName="Williams, Reid &amp; Littlewood" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[405,584,1681,1706]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFE24F921FDDDF91F" box="[405,584,1681,1706]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Echinolittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although with only weak support (posterior probability of clade of remaining 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFEA4F908FDB6F967" box="[277,547,1720,1746]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFEA4F908FE5DF964" box="[277,456,1720,1745]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Echinolittorina</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
= 76%; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFD36F908FC0EF967" author="Williams, S. T. &amp; Duda, T. F." box="[647,923,1720,1746]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1618 - 1634" refId="ref73765" refString="Williams, S. T. &amp; Duda, T. F. (2008) Did tectonic activity stimulate Oligo-Miocene speciation in the Indo-West Pacific? Evolution, 62, 1618 - 1634." type="journal article" year="2008">Williams &amp; Duda 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="1341CDFCA504FF9AFC16F908FC7EF967" box="[935,1003,1720,1746]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1692,1716]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,692,1668]" captionTargetId="figure-365@6.[152,1435,692,1668]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Molecular phylogeny of all 60 known species of worldwide Echinolittorina (after Williams &amp; Duda 2008), with geographical distributions and subgeneric groups. This is a chronogram, produced by BEAST analysis of sequence data from 28S, 12S and COI genes, which employs Bayesian inference and an uncorrelated, relaxed, log-normal clock; error bars are 95% highest posterior density intervals, and numbers are Bayesian posterior probabilities (see Williams &amp; Duda 2008 for methods). The time calibration of the phylogeny may be underestimated; see Remarks on subgenus Echinolittorina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5318103" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5318103/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). If clustered within 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFB50F908FA01F964" baseAuthorityName="Williams, Reid &amp; Littlewood" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[1249,1428,1720,1745]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFB50F908FA01F964" box="[1249,1428,1720,1745]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Echinolittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the absence of penial glands and form of the outer marginal radular teeth are reconstructed as synapomorphies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFF77F8B5FD5CF8AA" authority="(Williams et al. 2003)" baseAuthorityName="Williams" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[198,713,1797,1823]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Fossarilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFF77F8B5FEEAF8AB" box="[198,383,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fossarilittorina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A504FF9AFE2FF8B5FD55F8AA" author="Williams, S. T. &amp; Reid, D. G. &amp; Littlewood, D. T. J." box="[414,704,1797,1823]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="60 - 86" refId="ref73842" refString="Williams, S. T., Reid, D. G. &amp; Littlewood, D. T. J. (2003) A molecular phylogeny of the Littorininae (Gastropoda: Littorinidae): unequal evolutionary rates, morphological parallelism and biogeography of the Southern Ocean. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 28, 60 - 86." type="journal article" year="2003">
Williams 
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFD90F8B5FDF1F8AB" box="[545,612,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but if the subgenus is basal these are equivocally symplesiomorphic. The combination of molecular and morphological evidence does tend to support the view that this subgeneric clade is sister to the remainder of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC5D179A504FF9BFF77F8C9FDB5FF4A" blockId="14.[151,1437,598,2016]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,152,719]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Although the absence of penial glandular disc and mamilliform penial gland, and the absence of the outer flange on the base of the outer marginal radular teeth are equivocal synapomorphies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA504FF9AFB20F810FADFF80C" box="[1169,1354,1952,1977]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Fossarilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA504FF9AFB20F810FADFF80C" box="[1169,1354,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fossarilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the topology of the latest molecular phylogeny the unequivocal synapomorphies can be listed as: shell sculpture smooth with single incised line; pseudumbilicus (shared with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA505FF9BFC56FF28FBF6FF04" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[999,1123,152,177]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="porcata">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA505FF9BFC56FF28FBF6FF04" box="[999,1123,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. porcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group); penial sperm duct closed as a tube by superficial epithelial fusion; additional gland around egg groove at posterior end of straight section of pallial oviduct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC5D179A505FF9BFF77FEBCFEC8FE2F" blockId="15.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This subgenus is known only from the tropical Atlantic Ocean. In addition to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA505FF9BFB12FEBCFAABFE90" authorityName="Potiez &amp; Michaud" authorityYear="1838" box="[1187,1342,268,293]" class="Gastropoda" family="Phasianellidae" genus="Phasianella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA505FF9BFB12FEBCFAABFE90" box="[1187,1342,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA505FF9BFA32FEBCFE9AFEFE" baseAuthorityName="Muhlfeld" baseAuthorityYear="1824" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mespillum">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA505FF9BFA32FEBCFE9AFEFE" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. mespillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is a third species, unnamed but sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA505FF9BFC9DFE82FC55FEFE" authorityName="Potiez &amp; Michaud" authorityYear="1838" box="[812,960,306,331]" class="Gastropoda" family="Phasianellidae" genus="Phasianella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA505FF9BFC9DFE82FC55FEFE" box="[812,960,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in West Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A505FF9BFB38FE82FA02FEF9" author="Williams, S. T. &amp; Reid, D. G." box="[1161,1431,306,332]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="2227 - 2251" refId="ref73800" refString="Williams, S. T. &amp; Reid, D. G. (2004) Speciation and diversity on tropical rocky shores: a global phylogeny of snails of the genus Echinolittorina. Evolution, 58, 2227 - 2251." type="journal article" year="2004">Williams &amp; Reid 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A505FF9BFF26FEE9FE2EFEC6" author="Williams, S. T. &amp; Duda, T. F." box="[151,443,345,371]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1618 - 1634" refId="ref73765" refString="Williams, S. T. &amp; Duda, T. F. (2008) Did tectonic activity stimulate Oligo-Miocene speciation in the Indo-West Pacific? Evolution, 62, 1618 - 1634." type="journal article" year="2008">Williams &amp; Duda 2008</bibRefCitation>
). No detailed account of the western Atlantic species has appeared since that by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A505FF9BFF26FE30FECFFE2F" author="Bequaert, J C" box="[151,346,384,410]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref64885" refString="Bequaert, J C. (1943). The genus Littorina in the Western Atlantic. Johnsonia, 1 (7), 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="1943">Bequaert (1943)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC5D179A505FF9BFF77FE16FBEAFD7A" blockId="15.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Unusually for the genus, these species occupy damp microhabitats and occur as low as the mid-eulittoral. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A505FF9BFF26FE7DFEFCFE52" author="Rosewater, J." box="[151,361,461,487]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="7 - 48" refId="ref71743" refString="Rosewater, J. (1981) The family Littorinidae in tropical West Africa. Atlantide Report, 13, 7 - 48." type="journal article" year="1981">Rosewater (1981)</bibRefCitation>
noted the resemblance of the shells to those of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA505FF9BFC7DFE7DFBDDFE53" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[972,1096,461,486]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="porcata">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA505FF9BFC7DFE7DFBDDFE53" box="[972,1096,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. porcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in the eastern Pacific. The latter are likewise small, umbilicate, and sometimes develop smooth shells, although spiral ribs are usually prominent (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A505FF9BFE32FDAAFD83FD81" author="Reid, D. G." box="[387,534,538,564]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="85 - 169" refId="ref71039" refString="Reid, D. G. (2002 b) The genus Nodilittorina von Martens, 1897 (Gastropoda: Littorinidae) in the eastern Pacific Ocean, with a discussion of biogeographic provinces of the rocky-shore fauna. Veliger, 45, 85 - 169." type="journal article" year="2002">Reid 2002b</bibRefCitation>
). They can be found nestling among barnacles (like 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA505FF9BFB10FDAAFAACFD86" authorityName="Potiez &amp; Michaud" authorityYear="1838" box="[1185,1337,538,563]" class="Gastropoda" family="Phasianellidae" genus="Phasianella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA505FF9BFB10FDAAFAACFD86" box="[1185,1337,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and in shallow pools (like all 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA505FF9BFE1FFDF1FDFDFDEF" box="[430,616,577,602]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Fossarilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA505FF9BFE1FFDF1FDFDFDEF" box="[430,616,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fossarilittorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which may explain their convergent shell form. In the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA505FF9BFAAFFDF1FA09FDEF" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[1310,1436,577,602]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Echinolittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="porcata">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA505FF9BFAAFFDF1FA09FDEF" box="[1310,1436,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. porcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group it has been argued that smooth shells are an ecophenotypic response to permanent submergence in pools (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEBAC88A505FF9BFF2EFD3EFEA4FD1D" author="Reid, D. G." box="[159,305,654,680]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="85 - 169" refId="ref71039" refString="Reid, D. G. (2002 b) The genus Nodilittorina von Martens, 1897 (Gastropoda: Littorinidae) in the eastern Pacific Ocean, with a discussion of biogeographic provinces of the rocky-shore fauna. Veliger, 45, 85 - 169." type="journal article" year="2002">Reid 2002b</bibRefCitation>
). There is no indication of a similar effect in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7AAAFAA505FF9BFCD4FD3FFB14FD1D" box="[869,1153,654,680]" class="Gastropoda" family="Littorinidae" genus="Fossarilittorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B90E0D6BA505FF9BFCD4FD3FFB8BFD1D" box="[869,1054,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fossarilittorina</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, but this does hint that smooth shells may be adaptive in these species that occur relatively low on the shore.
</paragraph>
